HEADWORD: Mousehole
<hw>Mouse"hole`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hole made by a
mouse, for passage or abode, as in a wall; hence, a very small hole like
that gnawed by a mouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mousekin</ent>⟦br⟧
